gov.nih.nlm.meme.common
Interface MEMEString

All Known Subinterfaces:
Atom
All Known Implementing Classes:
Atom.Default, MEMEString.Default
public interface MEMEString

Generically represents the strings used for atom names in the MEME database. Rougly, it represents the data in the string_ui table. Most of the methods in this interface are accessors for the various kinds of information associated with a string, including:

  • SUI: The string unique identifier associated with a case-sensitive string
  • ISUI: The string unique identifier associated with a case-insensitive string
  • LUI: The lexical class identifier associated with a normalized representation of the string (produced by the lvg luiNorm program)
  • String: The actual case-sensitive string itself
  • NormalizedString: The normalized string

The other methods are used to assertain various properties of the strings. The getBaseString(), isBaseString(), getBracketNumber(), and isBracketString() methods are all useful in disecting the multiple-meaning disambiguating strings which end with a number in brackets. For example, suppose getString() returned this string:

This is a sample string <5>

In this case, the getBaseString() method would return the string stripped of its bracket number:

This is a sample string

The getBracketNumber() method would return the number in the brackets, or 5. The isBaseString() would return false since the string ends with a bracket, and isBracketString() which is the inverse would return true.

MEME Group

getBaseString

public String getBaseString()
Returns the string stripped of any bracket number. this is equivalent to (in perl) getString() =~ s/ <\d{1,}>$//;.

Returns:
the string stripped of any bracket number

isBaseString

public boolean isBaseString()
Indicates whether or not this is base string.

Returns:

getBracketNumber

public int getBracketNumber()
Returns the bracket number. In a string like "Apple <5>" this would be the int 5. In a string with no brackets, like "Apple", it returns 0.

Returns:
the int bracket number

isBracketString

public boolean isBracketString()
Indicates whether or not this is bracket string.
